snippet.textDisplay:
It’s so interesting to me how people react to lakers games. It seems you have lebron/laker fans, like big time fans, who aren’t very objective and always make excuses for lebron and lakers, and then you have laker/lebron haters, who go even further in the opposite direction and discredit anything positive the lakers or lebron does and intensify the magnitude of any laker or lebron mistake. Why aren’t there more people in the middle? Like people who let’s say, root for the heat, or lakers, root for one of those teams to win, but at the same time still judge the happenings of the game objectively. Every blue moon I see a post from someone who isn’t a fan of lebron, but defends him or gives him credit, or is a fan of the lakers, but discusses some of their shortcomings or things they have seen the team do that are a little worrisome. I really appreciate that but it seems to be very minimal. I’m just not sure if people either WANT to be biased, think they are legit supposed to be biased if it’s their favorite team, or a just blind to how unfair they are being and have such poor perspective, such “world revolves around me” perspective that they literally cannot see when they are being so clearly biased. Like when someone who’s YouTube name is “LeCHOKE” argues in a comment about how overrated lebron is on a video of lebron dropping 39/15/13 in a big win. It’s like..do they not realize what they are doing? My guess is that most of it is due to blindness of truth. And these are the areas where I think even something such as your sports fandom can reveal so much about you as a person. Like IMO it is very easy to tell if someone is insecure, repressed, depressed, resentful etc in many areas of their life just based on how they perceive certain events and players in sports. I think it is a bit ironic that so many people are so selfish and self centered and egotistical, but act this way mostly due to damaged and tiny little egos. It’s like think of that dude who does anything he can do to make himself look as manly as possible. He grows a beard and never trims it. Makes sure everyone knows that he doesn’t care what he looks like and when he shops he intentionally buys anything that makes him look like he doesn’t care about style. When he gets his hair cut it’s got to be something generic but also something very mentally, often resembling a militaristic style. He speaks fondly of his skills with women. Says evethring can be solved by mind over matter. Says feelings don’t exist. Makes many jokes whenever he sees someone who is LGBTQ, like legit cannot let it go and continues to verbally abuse them, or at least from a distance and to the people he hangs out with. He also picks on any man he comes across who appears to take good care of themselves physically if any of their stylistic choices are metrosexual. Pretty much he picks on any man who is objectively good looking and enjoys dressing well. He refers to any man who is good looking in any other way than “rough and rugged” by calling them gay. Asking them if they are gay. Even after meeting women they have slept with and having them confirm that they are heterosexual many times, will continue to assert and badger the man about how he just be gay, almost obsessively. He will act like this, almost obsessed, to any man who resembles anything feminine, or not even feminine but just handsome in a way that isn’t super “manly”. Then 3 years later, it turns out that this man was secretly bi sexual or homosexual himself, had issues getting erections with women, and had secretly slept with a man during every single heterosexual relationship he had been in.
Y’all get what I’m saying? I’m sure you know of at least one dude like that. Or perhaps it is you? If it is, not trying to hate on you, just telling you that to some of us, perhaps not many, it is so obvious what you are doing and what you are repressing. The same way it’s so obvious that we can’t take anyone’s opinion seriously when their name is “le-3-6” and you start hating on lebron. No one will ever take you seriously, and as I stated I’m really just curious as to why people are so openly biased. Jealousy obviously plays a huge factor in all of this as well, but I think That can just be stored away under the insecurity part. Idk maybe people just enjoy being biased in all areas of their life. They enjoy always looking outward when bad things happen in their life, refusing to look at themselves first. Maybe this is all part of the “ignorance is bliss” that I just will never get to “enjoy”. I can’t imagine living a life where I truly think I’m the center of the universe and the only thing that matters is me and what is best for me. I don’t get how anyone can live a life that selfish. How do you live with yourself being that way? How can you have no empathy? How can you care so little about the truth? Not my truth, your truth, but the overall TRUTH. Idk. Maybe it’s all fear based and it really is about being sooo unsure of what is real and what is true in this crazy universe we live in and then repressing that so much that you just never ever stop to ask anymore. Maybe that’s it? Like how does one get to the point where ignorance is bliss? I can’t just all of a sudden be ingroant even if I wanted to. It’s wild to me that I am the same species as people who are able to live this way. I’m not “better” or “worse” than them. I’m just so differnt. I read so many comments on these pages that just blow my mind.
